  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in the clay tagine over medium heat.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger and cook until fragrant.",
    "Add the lamb cubes and cook until browned on all sides.",
    "Add the katsuramuki-cut red chilli, cumin, coriander, paprika, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Add 1 cup of water to the tagine and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours, or until the lamb is tender.",
    "Serve the lamb tagine hot, garnished with fresh herbs, if desired."
